# Production Deploy Runbook

End-to-end guide for taking `{{PROJECT_NAME}}` from an empty GCP project to a
live service. Follow top-to-bottom on first deploy. Sections 9+ are
day-2 operations.

`infra/README.md` is the quick-reference card. **This document is the
step-by-step** — every command is copy-pasteable, every step has a
verification, every failure mode has a recovery.

---

## 0. Conventions

Set these shell variables once at the top of every session. Every command
below assumes they exist.

```bash
export PROJECT_ID="your-gcp-project-id"
export REGION="europe-west1"
export SERVICE_NAME="{{PROJECT_NAME}}"
export REPOSITORY="{{PROJECT_NAME}}"
export SQL_INSTANCE="{{PROJECT_NAME}}-pg"
export DB_NAME="{{PROJECT_NAME}}"
export DB_USER="{{PROJECT_NAME}}"
export GCS_BUCKET="{{PROJECT_NAME}}-prod-eu"
export TASKS_QUEUE="{{PROJECT_NAME}}-jobs"
export GITHUB_OWNER="your-github-org"
export GITHUB_REPO="{{PROJECT_NAME}}"

gcloud config set project "$PROJECT_ID"
```

If a step references `<PLACEHOLDER>` instead of `$VAR`, you must read its
value from the previous step's output. Never hard-code secrets in scripts.

---

## 1. Pre-flight checks

Before touching GCP, confirm:

- [ ] You have `roles/owner` or equivalent on `$PROJECT_ID` (or each
      individual role listed in §3.1).
- [ ] `gcloud` CLI ≥ 470.0.0 (`gcloud --version`).
- [ ] `gh` CLI ≥ 2.40 authenticated (`gh auth status`).
- [ ] Billing is enabled on the GCP project
      (`gcloud beta billing projects describe "$PROJECT_ID"`).
- [ ] You have completed every "blocks deploy = Yes" row from `ACCOUNTS.md`.
- [ ] Local repo at the commit you intend to deploy.
      `git rev-parse HEAD` ↔ matches CI green on main.

Skip any of these and a later step will fail in a harder-to-debug way.

