## 5. First deploy via GitHub Actions

### 5.1 Workload Identity Federation

GitHub Actions authenticates to GCP without long-lived JSON keys.

```bash
# Create the pool
gcloud iam workload-identity-pools create github-actions \
  --location=global \
  --display-name="GitHub Actions"

# Create the OIDC provider inside the pool
gcloud iam workload-identity-pools providers create-oidc github \
  --location=global \
  --workload-identity-pool=github-actions \
  --display-name="GitHub OIDC" \
  --issuer-uri=https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com \
  --attribute-mapping="google.subject=assertion.sub,attribute.actor=assertion.actor,attribute.repository=assertion.repository" \
  --attribute-condition="assertion.repository=='${GITHUB_OWNER}/${GITHUB_REPO}'"

# Allow the GitHub repo to impersonate the deploy SA
PROJECT_NUMBER=$(gcloud projects describe "$PROJECT_ID" --format='value(projectNumber)')
gcloud iam service-accounts add-iam-policy-binding \
  "${DEPLOY_SA}" \
  --role=roles/iam.workloadIdentityUser \
  --member="principalSet://iam.googleapis.com/projects/${PROJECT_NUMBER}/locations/global/workloadIdentityPools/github-actions/attribute.repository/${GITHUB_OWNER}/${GITHUB_REPO}"
```

Get the provider resource name (you'll need it as a GitHub secret):

```bash
PROVIDER="projects/${PROJECT_NUMBER}/locations/global/workloadIdentityPools/github-actions/providers/github"
echo "GCP_WORKLOAD_IDENTITY_PROVIDER=$PROVIDER"
```

### 5.2 GitHub repo secrets and variables

Set these via `gh` or the web UI. Secrets first:

```bash
gh secret set GCP_PROJECT --body "$PROJECT_ID" --repo "$GITHUB_OWNER/$GITHUB_REPO"
gh secret set GCP_WORKLOAD_IDENTITY_PROVIDER --body "$PROVIDER" --repo "$GITHUB_OWNER/$GITHUB_REPO"
gh secret set GCP_DEPLOY_SERVICE_ACCOUNT --body "$DEPLOY_SA" --repo "$GITHUB_OWNER/$GITHUB_REPO"
```

Stripe price IDs are *not secret* but are environment-specific. Add them as
**repo variables** so the deploy workflow can substitute them.

> **Note:** `infra/cloud_run.yaml` does not currently substitute these. If
> the prices need to live in the service spec, add `__STRIPE_PRICE_<TIER>__`
> placeholders to `cloud_run.yaml` and a matching `sed` step in
> `deploy.yml`.

### 5.3 Trigger the deploy

Two options.

**A. Via `gh` CLI:**
```bash
gh workflow run deploy.yml --repo "$GITHUB_OWNER/$GITHUB_REPO" \
  -f environment=staging
# Watch:
gh run watch --repo "$GITHUB_OWNER/$GITHUB_REPO"
```

**B. Via the web UI:** Actions → Deploy to Cloud Run → Run workflow → pick
`staging` or `production`.

**Verify:** The final workflow step is "Smoke check" — it must return
`Healthy`. If it doesn't, see §10.

```bash
SERVICE_URL=$(gcloud run services describe "$SERVICE_NAME" \
  --region="$REGION" --format='value(status.url)')
echo "$SERVICE_URL"
curl -sf "$SERVICE_URL/healthz" -m 5 ; echo
# Expected: {"status":"ok"}
```

