## 9. End-to-end smoke test

Exercise a full happy path through your production service. For each
critical pipeline stage, identify:

| Stage | Where to check | Expected |
|---|---|---|
| Webhook received | Cloud Run logs | `POST /webhook 200` |
| Job created | DB | row with `status='queued'` |
| Cloud Task enqueued | Cloud Tasks console | task visible in the queue |
| Worker dispatched | Cloud Run logs | `POST /worker/process 200` |
| Pipeline ran | Logs | each stage transition logged |
| Output delivered | end-user surface | the user sees the expected result |
| Job marked done | DB | `status='done'` |
| Usage tracked | usage / metering table | counter incremented |

If any of these fail, see §10.

