## 10. Common failures and recovery

### 10.1 `/healthz` returns 503 right after deploy

Most likely the secret mount failed (a referenced secret has no version,
or the runtime SA lacks `secretmanager.secretAccessor`).

```bash
# Check the latest revision's status
gcloud run revisions list \
  --service="$SERVICE_NAME" --region="$REGION" \
  --format='table(name,status.conditions[0].type,status.conditions[0].message)' \
  --limit=3
```

Look for a `ContainerHealthy: False` row. Fix the underlying secret or
IAM binding, then redeploy (§5.3).

### 10.2 Identity-provider webhook returns 401

The provider says the webhook is rejecting requests. Almost always the
shared secret stored in Secret Manager doesn't match what's configured at
the provider. Either re-register the webhook with the right value, or
update Secret Manager + redeploy.

### 10.3 Worker returns 401 to Cloud Tasks

`POST /worker/process 401` in Cloud Run logs. Cloud Tasks OIDC audience
mismatch. Verify the audience claim matches your worker URL.

```bash
gcloud run services describe "$SERVICE_NAME" --region="$REGION" \
  --format='value(spec.template.spec.containers[0].env)' \
  | tr ';' '\n' | grep WORKER_PROCESS_URL
```

If it's empty or doesn't match the service's actual URL, edit
`infra/cloud_run.yaml` to set `WORKER_PROCESS_URL` explicitly and
redeploy.

### 10.4 Cloud SQL connection refused

```
sqlalchemy.exc.OperationalError: connection refused
```

The `cloudsql-instances` annotation in `cloud_run.yaml` must contain the
correct `__PROJECT__:europe-west1:{{PROJECT_NAME}}-pg` triple. The deploy
workflow's sed substitution should handle this. Verify:

```bash
gcloud run services describe "$SERVICE_NAME" --region="$REGION" \
  --format='value(metadata.annotations,spec.template.metadata.annotations)' \
  | grep cloudsql
```

If the value is literal `__PROJECT__`, the substitution didn't run —
re-trigger the workflow.

### 10.5 Stripe webhook signature error

`POST /api/webhooks/stripe 400 "Invalid signature"`. Either:

- The webhook secret in Secret Manager doesn't match Stripe (you regenerated
  it in Stripe and forgot to update Secret Manager).
- A body-modifying proxy is in front of Cloud Run (Cloud Armor, custom
  domain redirect that strips request body) — Stripe signs the *raw* body.

Fix: refresh `{{PROJECT_NAME}}-stripe-webhook-secret`, redeploy, retry the
test webhook.

